Sculptor->Primitives

This allows the user to insert basic objects (such as cones or
cylinders) into the scene. Double-clicking on the required item on the
list creates an object in the center of the scene. The user may use
this object unaltered, or resize it (see Direct/Slider manips) or
modify the geometry further using the Potter or Face Builder tool. The
object created is given a default name automatically, and displayed at
the top of the tool. The user can change this by deleting the name,
and typing in a new name.

A whole range of interesting basic shapes in supplied with Movieola ,
which can be used by the user as a starting shape for more complex
modeling.
